news.title: Bond trustee becomes new petitioner to liquidate China's Kaisa Group
news.para: The latest development came after Broad Peak Investment, which filed the winding-up petition in July in relation to non-payment of onshore bonds worth 170 million yuan ($24 million), sought to withdraw from the case as it has sold the debt holdings earlier this year.

news.title: China Evergrande liquidators appoint legal advisers: Sources
news.para: Global firm Clifford Chance and Hong Kong firms Tanner De Witt and Karas So were mandated recently to provide legal advice on the liquidation, which has been under way for about six weeks, the people added.

news.title: Ghaziabad master plan hits a hurdle fourth time, over green zone now
news.para: The Master Plan 2021, which was to stay in effect until the end of the 2021 financial year, is likely to remain in effect until the new plan is approved by state officials.

news.title: Maharashtra direct KDMC to impose property tax from 27 villages residents as per before 2017 rates
news.para: In a meeting held at Mumbai, the Chief Minister directed Kalyan-Dombivli Municipal Corporation to impose property tax at old rates for residents of 27 villages within its limits.

news.title: Noida: 1,500 stamp duty evasion cases, camp on March 16 to resolve issues
news.para: In Noida and Greater Noida, the properties are registered in different categories like residential, commercial, industrial, institutional, agricultural, etc. Hence, a person cannot use the residential area for commercial activity or any other use.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to auction 13 properties on March 28 for tax default
news.para: Four properties from Wadmukhwadi in Charholi, three each from Nigdi and Tathawade, and one property each from Sangvi, Pimpri and Pimple Nilakh have been put up for auction.

news.title: Residents in fringes owe Pune civic body Rs 1,246 crore in property tax dues
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) had organised a drive to seal properties of defaulters. But it was stopped after residents met guardian minister Ajit Pawar and demanded a discount on the taxes.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body extends seven years property tax exemption to Imagicaa
news.para: The civic body had rejected the same tender earlier as it had received only one bid . The same bidder, Imagicaa, who had applied earlier had applied again this time and awarded the contract.

news.title: Manesar civic body to conduct drone survey to identify illegal colonies
news.para: The first phase of the survey will aim at identifying unauthorised and authorised colonies. Bas Kushla, Bas Haria and Dhana are among the villages that will be covered in the first phase.

news.title: NCDRC orders NBCC India to refund NBCC Green View Apartment residents
news.para: NBCC India has been directed to refund entire amount deposited by the residents of NBCC Green View Apartment with interest @9% per annum.

news.title: NCLT rejects Express Group of Hotels' revival plan for Neesa Leisure
news.para: The company has admitted liabilities of Rs 1,580 crore, whereas the resolution plan approved by the lenders proposed to give Rs 150 crore to them to acquire the company through the bankruptcy process.

news.title: Pune civic body plans rental housing for floating population
news.para: A PMC official said the administration was also planning an affordable housing project and a slum rehabilitation project in Gultekdi, where PMC has 21 acres of land.

news.title: Lawyers meet Haryana RERA chairman, want an alternative dispute redress panel
news.para: The bar and Rera bench compliment each other and proper coordination and understanding between them is a sine qua non for efficient grievance redress and justice delivery system. Therefore, we met on Wednesday,” Rera chief Kumar said.

news.title: Telangana RERA asks buyers to purchase land approved by GHMC, DTCP or HMDA
news.para: The announcement comes in the wake of proposed sale of flats by Buildox in Hafizpet, wherein the representatives of Buildox and the complainants were ordered to appear for investigation.

news.title: Multiple metro projects to boost connectivity in Haryana
news.para: According to an official statement, the HMRTC is making substantial strides in advancing multiple metro projects across the state, with the aim of fortifying connectivity and enriching public transportation alternatives.

news.title: Juhu residents seek solution to 'severe pollution' due to construction works
news.para: Gulmohar Area Societies Welfare Group members and locals met K-West ward’s assistant commissioner Prithviraj Chauhan and his team after local MLA Ameet Satam arranged a meeting for them

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA certification must for all real estate agents
news.para: It is mandatory to obtain certificate after training for new agents seeking RERA registration. This condition is applicable for already registered RERA agents and they have been given one year time to acquire training and obtain certificate else their RERA registration will be cancelled.
